								=======================

=> This method is used to get Runtime instance of class.



package in.psa.dev;

import java.lang.reflect.Method;

public class Student {

	public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
		
		
		Student s = new Student();//obj creation
		Class cls= s.getClass();
	  
		 System.out.println(cls.getName());
		 System.out.println(s.getClass().getName());//this is called method chaining
		 
		 
		 //another approach to create a object 
		 
		 Object object = cls.newInstance();//2nd approach to create object 
		 System.out.println(object);	 
	}

}
												
												=============================
												    4.clone() method
												=============================

=> This method is used to create duplicate object for the given object.
=>If we want to clone any object then that class should implement Cloneable interface which is marker interface.
=> If your class implements Cloneable interface then only JVM will allow you to clone the object.


package students;




public class Student1 implements Cloneable{
	
	public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
		
		
		Student1 s = new Student1();
		System.out.println(s);
		
		Object clone = s.clone();//cloning (another approch to create obj for a class )
		System.out.println(clone);
	}

}




OutPut: 	students.Student1@65b3120a
            students.Student1@6f539caf





